                                <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">How is EMI calculated?</summary>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">EMI is calculated using the formula: <span class="font-mono">EMI = [P x R x (1+R)^N]/[(1+R)^N-1]</span>, where P is the principal, R is the monthly interest rate, and N is the number of monthly installments.</p>
                            </details>
                            <details class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                                <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">What factors affect my EMI?</summary>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">Your EMI depends on three factors: the loan amount, the interest rate, and the loan tenure. A longer tenure reduces your EMI but increases the total interest paid.</p>
                            </details>
                        </div>
